Nothing to sorry.

\\Could explain me about the "deque"?
\The event queue is a first in, first out queue.
\The idea behind "deque" is "get the next event that is waiting in the queue." We wanted to say "get an event" but
\that would call the routine that is used for looping through a list, which is different, so we needed a special word.
\Our "deque" should have been "de-queue", but we spelled it wrong, thinking "deque" was just a modern spelling of "dequeue".
Found that "deque" is an alternate spelling, indeed. But the many uses were confusing.
Now it is clearer for me.

\ \In Spanish there are not a convention for this, but I choose "desencolar" (des-encolar, i.e. to de-queue),
\Both "desencolar un evento"  and "esperar un evento" added to El Seso.
\I put "Esperar un evento" in the Sal Monet and Sal Monet Instructions. Let me know if you don't like that.
Really fine.

